ue based on metric learning . In ICASSP 2025-2025 IEEE International Conference on Acoustics, Speech and Signal Processing (ICASSP) , pp. 1–5 . Cited by: §5.1.1 . [34] T. Xiao, B. Xu, and C. Zhao (2023) Spatially selective active noise control systems . The Journal of the Acoustical Society of America 153 ( 5 ), pp. 2733–2733 . Cited by: §1 . [35] R. Xie, A. Tu, C. Shi, S. Elliott, H. Li, and L. Zhang (2024) Cognitive virtual sensing technique for feedforward active noise control . In ICASSP 2024-2024 IEEE International Conference on Acoustics, Speech and Signal Processing (ICASSP) , pp. 981–985 . Cited by: §1 . [36] W. Yang, S. Li, and X. Luo (2024) Data driven vibration control: a review . IEEE/CAA Journal of Automatica Sinica 11 ( 9 ), pp. 1898–1917 . Cited by: §1 . [37] H. Zhang and D. Wang (2021) Deep anc: a deep learning approach to active noise control . Neural Networks 141 , pp. 1–10 . Cited by: §1 . [38] H. Zhang, J. Zhang, F. Ma, P. N. Samarasinghe, and H. Sun (2023) A time-domain multi-channel directional active noise control system . In 2023 31st European Signal Processing Conference (EUSIPCO) , pp. 376–380 . Cited by: §1 . [39] J. Zhang, T. D. Abhayapala, W. Zhang, P. N. Samarasinghe, and S. Jiang (2018) Active noise control over space: a wave domain approach . IEEE/ACM Transactions on audio, speech, and language processing 26 ( 4 ), pp. 774–786 . Cited by: §1 , §3 . [40] L. Zhang and X. Qiu (2014) Causality study on a feedforward active noise control headset with different noise coming directions in free field . Applied Acoustics 80 , pp. 36–44 . Cited by: §1 . [41] Y. Zhao, Y. Zhang, L. Guo, S. Ding, and X. Wang (2025) Advances in machine learning-based active vibration control for automotive seat suspensions: a comprehensive review . Mechanical Systems and Signal Processing 231 , pp. 112645 . Cited by: §1 . Experimental support, please view the build logs for errors. Generated by L A T E xml . Instructions for reporting errors We are continuing to im