{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-92138560683ead81", "type": "tool_result", "content": "{\n    \"query\": \"generative fixed-filter active noise control GFANC deep learning SOTA 2025 2026\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) uses deep learning to generate control filters for effective noise reduction. It combines pre-trained sub filters to adapt to different noise types. GFANC is seen as a state-of-the-art method for active noise control.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://github.com/Luo-Zhengding/GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control\",\n            \"title\": \"GitHub - Luo-Zhengding/GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control: To overcome the limitation and obtain more appropriate control filters, a generative fixed-filter active noise control (GFANC) approach is proposed in this paper. Specifically, various control filters can be generated by using different hard weights to combine pre-trained sub control filters. The hard weights are automatically obtained via a one-dimensional convolutional neural network given the incoming noise. \\u00b7 GitHub\",\n            \"content\": \"Luo-Zhengding   /  **GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control**  Public. # Luo-Zhengding/GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control. | Disturbance\\\\_generation.py | Disturbance\\\\_generation.py |  |  |. | M5\\\\_Network.py | M5\\\\_Network.py |  |  |. | loading\\\\_real\\\\_wave\\\\_noise.py | loading\\\\_real\\\\_wave\\\\_noise.py |  |  |. # Generative-Fixed-filter-Active-Noise-Control-based-on-Deep-Learning (GFANC). This is the code of my ICASSP2023 paper \\\"Generative Fixed filter Active Noise Control based on Deep Learning\\\". To obtain more appropriate control filters for differen primary noises, a generative fixed-filter active noise control (GFANC) approach is proposed in this paper. we have provided the trained 1D CNN model, you can easily run the \\\"Noise\\\\_Cancellation\\\\_GFANC.ipynb\\\" file to get the noise reduction results. If you want to use the GFANC method on new acoustic paths only requires obtaining the corresponding broadband control filter and decomposing it into sub control filters. * Deep Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control. * Delayless Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control based on Deep Learning and Bayesian Filter. To overcome the limitation and obtain more appropriate control filters, a generative fixed-filter active noise control (GFANC) approach is proposed in this paper.\",\n            \"score\": 0.70067,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://dr.ntu.edu.sg/entities/publication/a1796476-1468-4598-b689-b2baa1ca1921\",\n            \"title\": \"Deep learning-based Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control: Transferability and implementation\",\n            \"content\": \"# Deep learning-based Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control: Transferability and implementation. The deep learning-based Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) method can generate suitable control filters for different noise types, achieving faster response and better noise reduction than conventional approaches. However, its transferability and practical performance have not yet been fully validated. In this paper, the deep learning-based GFANC method is implemented in an Active Noise Control (ANC) headphone using a dual-rate architecture: a lightweight Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) on a co-processor works alongside the real-time controller to ensure delayless noise control. A theoretical explanation of GFANC's transferability is also provided, demonstrating that the method can be adapted to different acoustic environments by using system-specific sub control filters while retaining the same trained CNN. Finally, both simulations and real-time experiments confirm that GFANC outperforms the Selective Fixed-Filter ANC (SFANC) method, the Filtered-x Least Mean Square (FxLMS) algorithm, and a commercial ANC algorithm.1. School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE).\",\n            \"score\": 0.6161283,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.apsipa.org/proceedings/2025/papers/APSIPA2025_P330.pdf\",\n            \"title\": \"Continual Learning-Based Selective Fixed-filter Active ...\",\n            \"content\": \"Active noise control (ANC) is a more powerful and effective technique compared to the traditional one, which is able to generate the anti-noise with the same\",\n            \"score\": 0.5407062,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/Delivery.cfm/18a633ca-10ab-48de-8844-2444859c67c4-MECA.pdf?abstractid=4837239&mirid=1\",\n            \"title\": \"GFANC-RL\",\n            \"content\": \"The recent Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) method achieves a good trade-off between noise reduction performance and system\",\n            \"score\": 0.53517187,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://openreview.net/pdf/cfde417ca9e21519d8d4d48115432be889a85707.pdf\",\n            \"title\": \"GFANC-RL\",\n            \"content\": \"Contents lists available at ScienceDirect Neural Networks journal homepage: www.elsevier.com/locate/neunet Full Length Article GFANC-RL: Reinforcement Learning-based Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control Zhengding Luo a,1, Haozhe Ma b,1, Dongyuan Shi a,\\u2217, Woon-Seng Gan a a Digital Signal Processing Lab, School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, Nanyang Technological University, Singapore b School of Computing, National University of Singapore, Singapore A R T I C L E I N F O Keywords: Active Noise Control Generative Fixed-filter ANC Reinforcement Learning Convolutional Neural Network A B S T R A C T The recent Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) method achieves a good trade-off between noise reduction performance and system stability. Additionally, different from adaptive algorithms, the GFANC method does not require the error signal to update the control filter during noise control, which minimizes the risk of divergence and increases its stability (Luo, Shi, Ji, Shen, & Gan, 2024). Finally, the optimized policy parameters \\ud835\\udf03\\u2217are used as the parameters of the 1D CNN in the GFANC-RL method for real-time noise control.\",\n            \"score\": 0.53342235,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 2.2,\n    \"request_id\": \"4a4ee8e4-fec2-45e8-8e04-8ebabe7c1e2a\"\n}", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "75aedf01-d1ed-4e27-b84b-5886640ead7c", "uuid": "a1ba2be0-d3e9-45d7-97e4-e11dcb96c3aa", "timestamp": "2026-07-15T11:46:33.384Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "{\n    \"query\": \"generative fixed-filter active noise control GFANC deep learning SOTA 2025 2026\",\n    \"follow_up_questions\": null,\n    \"answer\": \"Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) uses deep learning to generate control filters for effective noise reduction. It combines pre-trained sub filters to adapt to different noise types. GFANC is seen as a state-of-the-art method for active noise control.\",\n    \"images\": [],\n    \"results\": [\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://github.com/Luo-Zhengding/GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control\",\n            \"title\": \"GitHub - Luo-Zhengding/GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control: To overcome the limitation and obtain more appropriate control filters, a generative fixed-filter active noise control (GFANC) approach is proposed in this paper. Specifically, various control filters can be generated by using different hard weights to combine pre-trained sub control filters. The hard weights are automatically obtained via a one-dimensional convolutional neural network given the incoming noise. \\u00b7 GitHub\",\n            \"content\": \"Luo-Zhengding   /  **GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control**  Public. # Luo-Zhengding/GFANC-Generative-fixed-filter-active-noise-control. | Disturbance\\\\_generation.py | Disturbance\\\\_generation.py |  |  |. | M5\\\\_Network.py | M5\\\\_Network.py |  |  |. | loading\\\\_real\\\\_wave\\\\_noise.py | loading\\\\_real\\\\_wave\\\\_noise.py |  |  |. # Generative-Fixed-filter-Active-Noise-Control-based-on-Deep-Learning (GFANC). This is the code of my ICASSP2023 paper \\\"Generative Fixed filter Active Noise Control based on Deep Learning\\\". To obtain more appropriate control filters for differen primary noises, a generative fixed-filter active noise control (GFANC) approach is proposed in this paper. we have provided the trained 1D CNN model, you can easily run the \\\"Noise\\\\_Cancellation\\\\_GFANC.ipynb\\\" file to get the noise reduction results. If you want to use the GFANC method on new acoustic paths only requires obtaining the corresponding broadband control filter and decomposing it into sub control filters. * Deep Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control. * Delayless Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control based on Deep Learning and Bayesian Filter. To overcome the limitation and obtain more appropriate control filters, a generative fixed-filter active noise control (GFANC) approach is proposed in this paper.\",\n            \"score\": 0.70067,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://dr.ntu.edu.sg/entities/publication/a1796476-1468-4598-b689-b2baa1ca1921\",\n            \"title\": \"Deep learning-based Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control: Transferability and implementation\",\n            \"content\": \"# Deep learning-based Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control: Transferability and implementation. The deep learning-based Generative Fixed-Filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) method can generate suitable control filters for different noise types, achieving faster response and better noise reduction than conventional approaches. However, its transferability and practical performance have not yet been fully validated. In this paper, the deep learning-based GFANC method is implemented in an Active Noise Control (ANC) headphone using a dual-rate architecture: a lightweight Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) on a co-processor works alongside the real-time controller to ensure delayless noise control. A theoretical explanation of GFANC's transferability is also provided, demonstrating that the method can be adapted to different acoustic environments by using system-specific sub control filters while retaining the same trained CNN. Finally, both simulations and real-time experiments confirm that GFANC outperforms the Selective Fixed-Filter ANC (SFANC) method, the Filtered-x Least Mean Square (FxLMS) algorithm, and a commercial ANC algorithm.1. School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering (EEE).\",\n            \"score\": 0.6161283,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://www.apsipa.org/proceedings/2025/papers/APSIPA2025_P330.pdf\",\n            \"title\": \"Continual Learning-Based Selective Fixed-filter Active ...\",\n            \"content\": \"Active noise control (ANC) is a more powerful and effective technique compared to the traditional one, which is able to generate the anti-noise with the same\",\n            \"score\": 0.5407062,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/Delivery.cfm/18a633ca-10ab-48de-8844-2444859c67c4-MECA.pdf?abstractid=4837239&mirid=1\",\n            \"title\": \"GFANC-RL\",\n            \"content\": \"The recent Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) method achieves a good trade-off between noise reduction performance and system\",\n            \"score\": 0.53517187,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        },\n        {\n            \"url\": \"https://openreview.net/pdf/cfde417ca9e21519d8d4d48115432be889a85707.pdf\",\n            \"title\": \"GFANC-RL\",\n            \"content\": \"Contents lists available at ScienceDirect Neural Networks journal homepage: www.elsevier.com/locate/neunet Full Length Article GFANC-RL: Reinforcement Learning-based Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control Zhengding Luo a,1, Haozhe Ma b,1, Dongyuan Shi a,\\u2217, Woon-Seng Gan a a Digital Signal Processing Lab, School of Electrical and Electronic Engineering, Nanyang Technological University, Singapore b School of Computing, National University of Singapore, Singapore A R T I C L E I N F O Keywords: Active Noise Control Generative Fixed-filter ANC Reinforcement Learning Convolutional Neural Network A B S T R A C T The recent Generative Fixed-filter Active Noise Control (GFANC) method achieves a good trade-off between noise reduction performance and system stability. Additionally, different from adaptive algorithms, the GFANC method does not require the error signal to update the control filter during noise control, which minimizes the risk of divergence and increases its stability (Luo, Shi, Ji, Shen, & Gan, 2024). Finally, the optimized policy parameters \\ud835\\udf03\\u2217are used as the parameters of the 1D CNN in the GFANC-RL method for real-time noise control.\",\n            \"score\": 0.53342235,\n            \"raw_content\": null\n        }\n    ],\n    \"response_time\": 2.2,\n    \"request_id\": \"4a4ee8e4-fec2-45e8-8e04-8ebabe7c1e2a\"\n}", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
